er%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Indian%20Jujube)%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekhejri%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Ejaal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Pilu%20Tree)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekumatiya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Acacia%20Senegal)%2C%20which%20are%20native%20to%20the%20region.%20%E2%80%9CChinkaras%20and%20blackbucks%20love%20%3Cem%3Eber%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20lot%2C%20so%20we%20plant%20those%20every%20year%20to%20replant%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F60652%2Ffighting-deforestation-oran-rajasthan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20lands%20of%20Oran%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrans%20%E2%80%94%20sacred%20groves%20that%20have%20traditionally%20been%20protected%20by%20rural%20communities%20%E2%80%94%20play%20a%20central%20role%20in%20Sharvan%E2%80%99s%20conservation%20efforts.%20These%20groves%20are%20rich%20in%20biodiversity%20and%20often%20include%20water%20bodies%20that%20are%20crucial%20for%20the%20survival%20of%20local%20wildlife.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Sharvan%E2%80%99s%20significant%20breakthroughs%20came%20when%20he%20and%20his%20team%20began%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20water%20ponds.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20ponds%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20for%20the%20animals%20to%20drink%20from%20were%20being%20dug%20too%20deep%20for%20them%20to%20reach%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20This%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20smaller%20animals%2C%20like%20rabbits%2C%20to%20access%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20inspiration%20from%20the%20shallow%20saucer-like%20ponds%20he%20had%20seen%20at%20Tal%20Chhapar%20Sanctuary%20in%20Nagaur%2C%20Sharvan%20and%20his%20team%2C%20with%20funding%20from%20Intact%20(Chapter%20Jodhpur)%20built%20shallow%20water%20ponds%20in%20the%20Orans%2C%20making%20them%20accessible%20to%20a%20wider%20variety%20of%20wildlife.%20The%20results%20were%20immediate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%